provision of inaccurate or false information;

c. the importance for financial consumers to ensure that the proposal form is
completed accurately as it forms the basis of the insurance/takaful contract;

d. period of coverage;

e. the importance of receiving and keeping the receipt from the FSP as proof of
payment of premium/takaful contribution by financial consumers; and

f. the time frame required by the FSP to issue a policy/takaful certificate.

